#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md
#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:8
msgid "Remote Procedure Calls (RPCs)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md
msgid ""
"Dash Core provides an RPC interface for administrative tasks, wallet "
"operations, and network/blockchain queries, with client libraries "
"available in multiple languages and a built-in dash-cli program for "
"command-line and RPC interaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:10
#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:9
#: ../../docs/core/dashcore/wallet-arguments-and-commands.md:10
#: ../../docs/core/examples/receiving-zmq-notifications.md:10
#: ../../docs/core/examples/testing-applications.md:57
#: ../../docs/core/guide/dash-features-instantsend.md:10
#: ../../docs/core/guide/dash-features.md:9
#: ../../docs/user/masternodes/understanding.rst:12
#: ../../docs/user/wallets/hardware.rst:89
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:12
msgid ""
"Dash Core provides a remote procedure call (RPC) interface for various "
"administrative tasks, [wallet](../resources/glossary.md#wallet) "
"operations, and queries about [network](../resources/glossary.md#network)"
" and [block chain](../resources/glossary.md#block-chain) data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:14
msgid ""
"Open-source client libraries for the RPC interface are readily available "
"in most modern programming languages, so you probably don't need to write"
" your own from scratch. Dash Core also ships with its own compiled C++ "
"RPC client, `dash-cli`, located in the `bin` directory alongside `dashd` "
"and `dash-qt`. The `dash-cli` program can be used as a command-line "
"interface (CLI) to Dash Core or for making RPC calls from applications "
"written in languages lacking a suitable native client. The remainder of "
"this section describes the Dash Core RPC protocol in detail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:17
msgid ""
"The following subsections reference setting configuration values. See the"
" [Examples Page](../examples/introduction.md) for more information about "
"setting Dash Core configuration values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:20
msgid "Enabling RPC"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:22
msgid ""
"If you start Dash Core using `dash-qt`, the RPC interface is disabled by "
"default. To enable it, set `server=1` in `dash.conf` or supply the "
"`-server` argument when invoking the program. If you start Dash Core "
"using `dashd`, the RPC interface is enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:24
msgid "Basic Security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:26
msgid ""
"The interface requires the user to provide a password for authenticating "
"RPC requests. This password can be set either using the `rpcpassword` "
"property in `dash.conf` or by supplying the `-rpcpassword` program "
"argument. Optionally a username can be set using the `rpcuser` "
"configuration value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:28
msgid "RPC-Auth Security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:30
msgid ""
"Alternatively, the authentication details can be provided using the "
"`rpcauth` property. This removes the need to include a plaintext password"
" in the `dash.conf` file by instead including a salt and hash of the "
"password along with a username in the format: `<USERNAME>:<SALT>$<HASH>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:39
msgid ""
"The `rpcauth` option can be specified multiple times if multiple users "
"are required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:42
msgid ""
"A canonical python script is included in Dash Core's repository under "
"[share/rpcuser](https://github.com/dashpay/dash/tree/master/share/rpcauth)"
" to generate the information required for the dash.conf file as well as "
"the password required by clients using the rpcauth name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:51
msgid "RPC Whitelist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:53
msgid ""
"The RPC whitelist system can limit certain RPC users to only have access "
"to some RPC calls. The system is configured by specifying the following "
"two parameters in the `dash.conf` file or by setting them as program "
"arguments on the command line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:55
msgid ""
"`rpcwhitelist`: set a whitelist to filter incoming RPC calls for a "
"specific user. The field <whitelist> comes in the format: "
"`<USERNAME>:<rpc 1>,<rpc 2>,...,<rpc n>`. If multiple whitelists are set "
"for a given user, they are set-intersected. Default whitelist behavior is"
" defined by `rpcwhitelistdefault`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:56
msgid "`rpcwhitelistdefault`: sets default behavior for RPC whitelisting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:57
msgid ""
"If `rpcwhitelistdefault` is set to `0`, users with an `rpcwhitelist` "
"entry are limited to their assigned RPCs. Other users can access any RPC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:58
msgid ""
"If `rpcwhitelistdefault` is set to `1`, RPC access is denied to all users"
" that do not have an `rpcwhitelist` entry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:60
#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:106
msgid "Example configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:73
msgid ""
"In this example, user1 can only call `getnetworkinfo`, user2 can only "
"call `getnetworkinfo` or `getwalletinfo`, while user3 can still call all "
"RPCs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:75
msgid "Restricted Access Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:77
msgid ""
"All RPC request restrictions are now configured using the [RPC whitelist "
"settings](#rpc-whitelist)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "<br>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:81
msgid ""
"Since Dash Core 0.17.0, an option is provided to add an RPC user that is "
"restricted to a small subset of RPCs used by Dash Platform. The "
"`platform-user` configuration value sets the name of the RPC user to be "
"restricted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:83
msgid ""
"The `platform-user` configuration value must be set to a previously "
"configured [rpcauth user](#rpc-auth-security)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:85
msgid "Only the following RPCs are accessible to the restricted user:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:87
msgid ""
"[`getbestblockhash`](../api/remote-procedure-calls-"
"blockchain.md#getbestblockhash)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:88
msgid "[`getblockhash`](../api/remote-procedure-calls-blockchain.md#getblockhash)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:89
msgid ""
"[`getblockcount`](../api/remote-procedure-calls-"
"blockchain.md#getblockcount)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:90
msgid ""
"[`getbestchainlock`](../api/remote-procedure-calls-"
"blockchain.md#getbestchainlock)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:91
msgid ""
"[`quorum sign 4`](../api/remote-procedure-calls-evo.md#quorum-sign) - The"
" restricted user can only request quorum signatures from the Platform "
"quorum (LLMQ type 4)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:92
msgid "[`quorum verify`](../api/remote-procedure-calls-evo.md#quorum-verify)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:93
msgid "[`verifyislock`](../api/remote-procedure-calls-evo.md#verifyislock)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:97
msgid "RPC Queue Priority"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:99
msgid ""
"Nodes receiving too many RPC requests may become unresponsive or be "
"banned if the load continues for too long. To mitigate this, Dash Core "
"21.0.0 introduced an additional RPC queue that can be used for lower-"
"priority requests. If the node becomes overloaded, low priority requests "
"are dropped so more important requests continue to receive responses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:101
msgid ""
"The system is configured by specifying the following parameters in the "
"`dash.conf` file or by setting them as program arguments on the command "
"line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:103
msgid ""
"`rpcexternaluser`: list of comma-separated usernames for JSON-RPC "
"external connections. If not specified, all requests use a single queue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:104
msgid ""
"`rpcexternalworkqueue`=<n>: - Set the depth of the work queue to service "
"external RPC calls (default: 16)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:113
msgid ""
"In this example, requests from external_user_1 and external_user_2 will "
"go to the lower-priority queue, while all other user request will go to "
"the standard queue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:115
msgid "Default Connection Info"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:117
msgid ""
"The Dash Core RPC service listens for HTTP `POST` requests on port 9998 "
"in [mainnet](../resources/glossary.md#mainnet) mode, 19998 in "
"[testnet](../resources/glossary.md#testnet), or 19898 in [regression test"
" mode](../resources/glossary.md#regression-test-mode). The port number "
"can be changed by setting `rpcport` in `dash.conf`. By default the RPC "
"service binds to your server's "
"[localhost](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Localhost) loopback network "
"interface so it's not accessible from other servers. Authentication is "
"implemented using [HTTP basic "
"authentication](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basic_access_authentication)."
" RPC HTTP requests must include a `Content-Type` header set to "
"`text/plain` and a `Content-Length` header set to the size of the request"
" body."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:119
msgid "Data Formats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:121
msgid ""
"The format of the request body and response data is based on [version 1.0"
" of the JSON-RPC specification](http://json-rpc.org/wiki/specification)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:123
msgid "Request Format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:125
msgid ""
"Specifically, the HTTP `POST` data of a request must be a JSON object "
"with the following format:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls-mining.md
#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "Request"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "The JSON-RPC request object"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "→ <br>`jsonrpc`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid ""
"Version indicator for the JSON-RPC request. Currently ignored by Dash "
"Core."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "→ <br>`id`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid ""
"An arbitrary string that will be returned with the response.  May be "
"omitted or set to an empty string (\"\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "→ <br>`method`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid ""
"The RPC method name (e.g. `getblock`).  See the RPC section for a list of"
" available methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "→ <br>`params`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid ""
"An array containing positional parameter values for the RPC.  May be an "
"empty array or omitted for RPC calls that don't have any required "
"parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid ""
"Starting from Dash Core 0.12.3 / Bitcoin Core 0.14.0 (replaces the params"
" array above) An object containing named parameter values for the RPC. "
"May be an empty object or omitted for RPC calls that don’t have any "
"required parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "→ → <br>Parameter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "*any*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "A parameter.  May be any JSON type allowed by the particular RPC method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:137
msgid ""
"In the table above and in other tables describing RPC input and output, "
"we use the following conventions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:139
msgid ""
"\"→\" indicates an argument that is the child of a JSON array or JSON "
"object. For example, \"→ → Parameter\" above means Parameter is the child"
" of the `params` array which itself is a child of the Request object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:141
msgid "Plain-text names like \"Request\" are unnamed in the actual JSON object"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:143
msgid ""
"Code-style names like `params` are literal strings that appear in the "
"JSON object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:145
msgid "\"Type\" is the JSON data type and the specific Dash Core type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:147
msgid ""
"\"Presence\" indicates whether or not a field must be present within its "
"containing array or object. Note that an optional object may still have "
"required children."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:149
msgid "Response Format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:151
msgid ""
"The HTTP response data for a RPC request is a JSON object with the "
"following format:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "Response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "The JSON-RPC response object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "→ <br>`result`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid ""
"The RPC output whose type varies by call.  Has value `null` if an error "
"occurred."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
msgid "→ <br>`error`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/remote-procedure-calls.md:79
