#: ../../docs/user/introduction/features.rst:435
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:94
msgid ""
"The socket type is PUB and the address must be a valid ZeroMQ socket "
"address. Each PUB notification has a topic and body, where the header "
"corresponds to the notification type. For instance, for the notification "
"`-zmqpubhashtx` the topic is `hashtx` (no null terminator) and the body "
"is the hexadecimal transaction hash (32 bytes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:97
msgid "The same address can be used in more than one notification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:100
msgid ""
"ZeroMQ endpoint specifiers for TCP (and others) are documented in the "
"[ZeroMQ API](http://api.zeromq.org/4-0:_start)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:102
msgid ""
"Client side, then, the ZeroMQ subscriber socket must have the "
"`ZMQ_SUBSCRIBE` option set to one or either of these prefixes (for "
"instance, just `hash`); without doing so will result in no messages "
"arriving. Please see the Dash Core repository for a [working "
"example](https://github.com/dashpay/dash/blob/master/contrib/zmq/zmq_sub3.4.py)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:104
#: ../../docs/core/reference/block-chain-block-headers.md
#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-special-transactions.md
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:106
msgid ""
"From the perspective of dashd, the ZeroMQ socket is write-only; PUB "
"sockets don't even have a read function. Thus, there is no state "
"introduced into dashd directly. Furthermore, no information is broadcast "
"that wasn't already received from the public P2P network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:108
msgid ""
"No authentication or authorization is done on connecting clients; it is "
"assumed that the ZeroMQ port is exposed only to trusted entities, using "
"other means such as firewalling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:110
msgid ""
"Note that when the block chain tip changes, a reorganisation may occur "
"and just the tip will be notified. It is up to the subscriber to retrieve"
" the chain from the last known block to the new tip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/api/zmq.md:112
msgid ""
"There are several possibilities that ZMQ notification can get lost during"
" transmission depending on the communication type your are using. Dashd "
"appends an up-counting sequence number to each notification which allows "
"listeners to detect lost notifications."
msgstr ""

