#: ../../docs/user/wallets/dashcore/coinjoin-instantsend.rst:265
#: ../../docs/user/wallets/hardware.rst:8 ../../docs/user/wallets/paper.rst:8
#: ../../docs/user/wallets/third-party.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/examples/introduction.md:10
msgid ""
"The following guide aims to provide examples to help you start building "
"Dash-based applications. To make the best use of this document, you may "
"want to install the current version of Dash Core, either from "
"[source](https://github.com/dashpay/dash/) or from a [pre-compiled "
"executable](https://www.dash.org/wallets/#wallets)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/examples/introduction.md:12
msgid ""
"Once installed, you'll have access to three programs: `dashd`, `dash-qt`,"
" and `dash-cli`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/examples/introduction.md:14
msgid ""
"`dash-qt` provides a combination full Dash "
"[peer](../resources/glossary.md#peer) and "
"[wallet](../resources/glossary.md#wallet) frontend. From the Help menu, "
"you can access a console where you can enter the RPC commands used "
"throughout this document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/examples/introduction.md:16
msgid ""
"`dashd` is more useful for programming: it provides a full peer which you"
" can interact with through RPCs to port 9998 (or 19998 for "
"[testnet](../resources/glossary.md#testnet) / 19898 for regtest)."
msgstr ""

