#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md
#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:7
msgid "Misbehaving Nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md
msgid ""
"Dash Core discourages peer nodes from sending false information by not "
"immediately disconnecting but by prioritizing them for eviction, with no "
"time-out or removal options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:10
msgid "Dash Core 18.1.0 introduced changes to how misbehaving peers are treated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:13
msgid ""
"Take note that for both types of broadcasting, mechanisms are in place to"
" punish misbehaving [peers](../resources/glossary.md#peer) who take up "
"bandwidth and computing resources by sending false information. Since "
"Dash Core 18.1.0, peers that misbehave (e.g. send us invalid blocks) are "
"referred to as discouraged nodes in log output. They are not strictly "
"banned: incoming connections are still allowed from them, but they're "
"preferred for eviction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:15
msgid ""
"Furthermore, a few additional changes are introduced to how discouraged "
"addresses are treated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:17
msgid ""
"Discouraging an address does not time out automatically after 24 hours "
"(or the `-bantime` setting). Depending on traffic from other peers, "
"discouragement may time out at an indeterminate time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:19
msgid "Discouragement is not persisted over restarts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:21
msgid ""
"There is no method to list discouraged addresses. They are not returned "
"by the [`listbanned` RPC](../api/remote-procedure-calls-"
"network.md#listbanned)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:23
msgid ""
"Discouragement cannot be removed with the [`setban remove` RPC](../api"
"/remote-procedure-calls-network.md#setban) command. If you need to remove"
" a discouragement, you can remove all discouragements by stopping and "
"restarting your node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/guide/p2p-network-misbehaving-nodes.md:25
msgid ""
"If a peer gets a banscore above the `-banscore=<n>` threshold (100 by "
"default), they will be disconnected and discouraged."
msgstr ""

