#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:86
msgid ""
"The [`filteradd` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#filteradd) tells the receiving "
"[peer](../resources/glossary.md#peer) to add a single element to a "
"previously-set [bloom filter](../resources/glossary.md#bloom-filter), "
"such as a new [public key](../resources/glossary.md#public-key). The "
"element is sent directly to the receiving peer; the peer then uses the "
"parameters set in the [`filterload` message](../reference/p2p-network-"
"control-messages.md#filterload) to add the element to the bloom filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:88
msgid ""
"Because the element is sent directly to the receiving peer, there is no "
"obfuscation of the element and none of the plausible-deniability privacy "
"provided by the bloom filter. Clients that want to maintain greater "
"privacy should recalculate the bloom filter themselves and send a new "
"[`filterload` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#filterload) with the recalculated bloom filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "element bytes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "The number of bytes in the following element field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "element"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "uint8_t[]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid ""
"The element to add to the current filter.  Maximum of 520 bytes, which is"
" the maximum size of an element which can be pushed onto the stack in a "
"pubkey or signature script.  Elements must be sent in the byte order they"
" would use when appearing in a raw transaction; for example, hashes "
"should be sent in internal byte order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:95
msgid ""
"Note: a [`filteradd` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#filteradd) will not be accepted unless a filter was "
"previously set with the [`filterload` message](../reference/p2p-network-"
"control-messages.md#filterload)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:97
msgid ""
"The annotated hexdump below shows a [`filteradd` message](../reference"
"/p2p-network-control-messages.md#filteradd) adding a "
"[TXID](../resources/glossary.md#transaction-identifiers). (The message "
"header has been omitted.) This TXID appears in the same block used for "
"the example hexdump in the [`merkleblock` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-data-messages.md#merkleblock); if that [`merkleblock` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md#merkleblock) is re-"
"sent after sending this [`filteradd` message](../reference/p2p-network-"
"control-messages.md#filteradd), six hashes are returned instead of four."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:105
msgid "filterclear"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:109
msgid ""
"The [`filterclear` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#filterclear) tells the receiving "
"[peer](../resources/glossary.md#peer) to remove a previously-set [bloom "
"filter](../resources/glossary.md#bloom-filter).  This also undoes the "
"effect of setting the relay field in the [`version` message](../reference"
"/p2p-network-control-messages.md#version) to 0, allowing unfiltered "
"access to [`inv` messages](../reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md#inv)"
" announcing new transactions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:111
msgid ""
"Dash Core does not require a [`filterclear` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#filterclear) before a replacement filter is "
"loaded with `filterload`.  It also doesn't require a [`filterload` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#filterload) before "
"a [`filterclear` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#filterclear)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:113
msgid ""
"There is no payload in a [`filterclear` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#filterclear).  See the [message header "
"section](../reference/p2p-network-message-headers.md) for an example of a"
" message without a payload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:115
msgid "filterload"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:119
msgid ""
"The [`filterload` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#filterload) tells the receiving "
"[peer](../resources/glossary.md#peer) to filter all relayed transactions "
"and requested [merkle blocks](../resources/glossary.md#merkle-block) "
"through the provided filter. This allows clients to receive transactions "
"relevant to their [wallet](../resources/glossary.md#wallet) plus a "
"configurable rate of false positive transactions which can provide "
"plausible-deniability privacy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "nFilterBytes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "Number of bytes in the following filter bit field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid ""
"A bit field of arbitrary byte-aligned size. The maximum size is 36,000 "
"bytes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "nHashFuncs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid ""
"The number of hash functions to use in this filter. The maximum value "
"allowed in this field is 50."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "nTweak"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid ""
"An arbitrary value to add to the seed value in the hash function used by "
"the bloom filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid "nFlags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md
msgid ""
"A set of flags that control how outpoints corresponding to a matched "
"pubkey script are added to the filter. See the table in the Updating A "
"Bloom Filter subsection below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:129
msgid ""
"The annotated hexdump below shows a [`filterload` message](../reference"
"/p2p-network-control-messages.md#filterload). (The message header has "
"been omitted.)  For an example of how this payload was created, see the "
"[filterload example](../examples/p2p-network-creating-a-bloom-filter.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:139
msgid "Initializing A Bloom Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:141
msgid ""
"Filters have two core parameters: the size of the bit field and the "
"number of hash functions to run against each data element. The following "
"formulas from BIP37 will allow you to automatically select appropriate "
"values based on the number of elements you plan to insert into the filter"
" (*n*) and the false positive rate (*p*) you desire to maintain plausible"
" deniability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:143
msgid ""
"Size of the bit field in bytes (*nFilterBytes*), up to a maximum of "
"36,000: `(-1 / log(2)**2 * n * log(p)) / 8`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:145
msgid ""
"Hash functions to use (*nHashFuncs*), up to a maximum of 50: "
"`nFilterBytes * 8 / n * log(2)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:148
msgid ""
"Note that the filter matches parts of transactions (transaction "
"elements), so the false positive rate is relative to the number of "
"elements checked---not the number of transactions checked. Each normal "
"transaction has a minimum of four matchable elements (described in the "
"comparison subsection below), so a filter with a false-positive rate of 1"
" percent will match about 4 percent of all transactions at a minimum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:150
msgid ""
"According to BIP37, the formulas and limits described above provide "
"support for bloom filters containing 20,000 items with a false positive "
"rate of less than 0.1 percent or 10,000 items with a false positive rate "
"of less than 0.0001 percent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:152
msgid ""
"Once the size of the bit field is known, the bit field should be "
"initialized as all zeroes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:154
msgid "Populating A Bloom Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:156
msgid ""
"The bloom filter is populated using between 1 and 50 unique hash "
"functions (the number specified per filter by the *nHashFuncs* field). "
"Instead of using up to 50 different hash function implementations, a "
"single implementation is used with a unique seed value for each function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:158
msgid ""
"The seed is `nHashNum * 0xfba4c795 + nTweak` as a *uint32\\_t*, where the"
" values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:160
msgid ""
"**nHashNum** is the sequence number for this hash function, starting at 0"
" for the first hash iteration and increasing up to the value of the "
"*nHashFuncs* field (minus one) for the last hash iteration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:162
msgid ""
"**0xfba4c795** is a constant optimized to create large differences in the"
" seed for different values of *nHashNum*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:164
msgid ""
"**nTweak** is a per-filter constant set by the client to require the use "
"of an arbitrary set of hash functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:166
msgid ""
"If the seed resulting from the formula above is larger than four bytes, "
"it must be truncated to its four most significant bytes (for example, "
"`0x8967452301 & 0xffffffff → 0x67452301`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:168
msgid ""
"The actual hash function implementation used is the [32-bit Murmur3 hash "
"function](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MurmurHash)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:171
msgid ""
"The Murmur3 hash function has separate 32-bit and 64-bit versions that "
"produce different results for the same "
"[input](../resources/glossary.md#input).  Only the 32-bit Murmur3 version"
" is used with Dash bloom filters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:174
msgid ""
"The data to be hashed can be any transaction element which the bloom "
"filter can match. See the next subsection for the list of transaction "
"elements checked against the filter. The largest element which can be "
"matched is a script data push of 520 bytes, so the data should never "
"exceed 520 bytes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:176
msgid ""
"The example below from Dash Core "
"[bloom.cpp](https://github.com/dashpay/dash/blob/v0.15.x/src/bloom.cpp#L59)"
" combines all the steps above to create the hash function template. The "
"seed is the first parameter; the data to be hashed is the second "
"parameter. The result is a uint32\\_t modulo the size of the bit field in"
" bits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:182
msgid ""
"Each data element to be added to the filter is hashed by *nHashFuncs* "
"number of hash functions. Each time a hash function is run, the result "
"will be the index number (*nIndex*) of a bit in the bit field. That bit "
"must be set to 1. For example if the filter bit field was `00000000` and "
"the result is 5, the revised filter bit field is `00000100` (the first "
"bit is bit 0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:184
msgid ""
"It is expected that sometimes the same index number will be returned more"
" than once when populating the bit field; this does not affect the "
"algorithm---after a bit is set to 1, it is never changed back to 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:186
msgid ""
"After all data elements have been added to the filter, each set of eight "
"bits is converted into a little-endian byte. These bytes are the value of"
" the *filter* field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:188
msgid "Comparing Transaction Elements To A Bloom Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:190
msgid ""
"To compare an arbitrary data element against the bloom filter, it is "
"hashed using the same parameters used to create the bloom filter. "
"Specifically, it is hashed *nHashFuncs* times, each time using the same "
"*nTweak* provided in the filter, and the resulting "
"[output](../resources/glossary.md#output) is modulo the size of the bit "
"field provided in the *filter* field.  After each hash is performed, the "
"filter is checked to see if the bit at that indexed location is set.  For"
" example if the result of a hash is `5` and the filter is `01001110`, the"
" bit is considered set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:193
msgid ""
"If the result of every hash points to a set bit, the filter matches. If "
"any of the results points to an unset bit, the filter does not match."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:195
msgid ""
"The following transaction elements are compared against bloom filters. "
"All elements will be hashed in the byte order used in "
"[blocks](../resources/glossary.md#block) (for example, "
"[TXIDs](../resources/glossary.md#transaction-identifiers) will be in "
"[internal byte order](../resources/glossary.md#internal-byte-order))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:197
msgid "**TXIDs:** the transaction's SHA256(SHA256()) hash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:199
msgid ""
"**Outpoints:** each 36-byte [outpoint](../resources/glossary.md#outpoint)"
" used this transaction's input section is individually compared to the "
"filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:201
msgid ""
"**Signature Script Data:** each element pushed onto the stack by a [data-"
"pushing opcode](../resources/glossary.md#data-pushing-opcode) in a "
"[signature script](../resources/glossary.md#signature-script) from this "
"transaction is individually compared to the filter.  This includes data "
"elements present in P2SH [redeem script](../resources/glossary.md#redeem-"
"script) when they are being spent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:203
msgid ""
"**PubKey Script Data:** each element pushed onto the the stack by a data-"
"pushing opcode in any [pubkey script](../resources/glossary.md#pubkey-"
"script) from this transaction is individually compared to the filter. (If"
" a pubkey script element matches the filter, the filter will be "
"immediately updated if the `BLOOM_UPDATE_ALL` flag was set; if the pubkey"
" script is in the P2PKH format and matches the filter, the filter will be"
" immediately updated if the `BLOOM_UPDATE_P2PUBKEY_ONLY` flag was set. "
"See the subsection below for details.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:205
msgid ""
"As of  Dash Core 0.14.0, elements in the extra payload section of "
"[DIP2](https://github.com/dashpay/dips/blob/master/dip-0002.md)-based "
"[special transactions](../resources/glossary.md#special-transactions) are"
" also compared against bloom filters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:207
msgid ""
"The following annotated hexdump of a transaction is from the [raw "
"transaction format section](../reference/transactions-raw-transaction-"
"format.md); the elements which would be checked by the filter are "
"emphasized in bold. Note that this transaction's TXID "
"(**`01000000017b1eab[...]`**) would also be checked, and that the "
"outpoint TXID and index number below would be checked as a single 36-byte"
" element."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:242
msgid "Updating A Bloom Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:244
msgid ""
"Clients will often want to track [inputs](../resources/glossary.md#input)"
" that spend [outputs](../resources/glossary.md#output) (outpoints) "
"relevant to their wallet, so the filterload field *nFlags* can be set to "
"allow the filtering [node](../resources/glossary.md#node) to update the "
"filter when a match is found. When the filtering node sees a [pubkey "
"script](../resources/glossary.md#pubkey-script) that pays a pubkey, "
"[address](../resources/glossary.md#address), or other data element "
"matching the filter, the filtering node immediately updates the filter "
"with the [outpoint](../resources/glossary.md#outpoint) corresponding to "
"that pubkey script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:246
msgid "![Automatically Updating Bloom Filters](../../img/dev/en-bloom-update.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:246
msgid "Automatically Updating Bloom Filters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:248
msgid ""
"If an input later spends that outpoint, the filter will match it, "
"allowing the filtering node to tell the client that one of its "
"transaction outputs has been spent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:250
msgid "The *nFlags* field has three allowed values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:170
msgid "`BLOOM_UPDATE_NONE`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:170
msgid "The filtering node should not update the filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:170
msgid "`BLOOM_UPDATE_ALL`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:170
msgid ""
"If the filter matches any data element in a pubkey script, the "
"corresponding outpoint is added to the filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:170
msgid "`BLOOM_UPDATE_P2PUBKEY_ONLY`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:170
msgid ""
"If the filter matches any data element in a pubkey script and that script"
" is either a P2PKH or non-P2SH pay-to-multisig script, the corresponding "
"outpoint is added to the filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:258
msgid ""
"In addition, because the filter size stays the same even though "
"additional elements are being added to it, the false positive rate "
"increases. Each false positive can result in another element being added "
"to the filter, creating a feedback loop that can (after a certain point) "
"make the filter useless. For this reason, clients using automatic filter "
"updates need to monitor the actual false positive rate and send a new "
"filter when the rate gets too high."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:260
msgid "getaddr"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:262
msgid ""
"The [`getaddr` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#getaddr) requests an [`addr` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#addr) from the receiving "
"[node](../resources/glossary.md#node), preferably one with lots of IP "
"addresses of other receiving nodes. The transmitting node can use those "
"IP addresses to quickly update its database of available nodes rather "
"than waiting for unsolicited [`addr` messages](../reference/p2p-network-"
"control-messages.md#addr) to arrive over time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:264
msgid ""
"There is no payload in a [`getaddr` message](../reference/p2p-network-"
"control-messages.md#getaddr).  See the [message header "
"section](../reference/p2p-network-message-headers.md) for an example of a"
" message without a payload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:266
msgid "getsporks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:268
msgid ""
"The [`getsporks` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#getsporks) requests [`spork` messages](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#spork) from the receiving node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:270
msgid ""
"There is no payload in a [`getsporks` message](../reference/p2p-network-"
"control-messages.md#getsporks).  See the [message header "
"section](../reference/p2p-network-message-headers.md) for an example of a"
" message without a payload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:272
msgid "ping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:274
msgid ""
"The [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#ping) "
"helps confirm that the receiving [peer](../resources/glossary.md#peer) is"
" still connected. If a TCP/IP error is encountered when sending the "
"[`ping` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#ping) (such"
" as a connection timeout), the transmitting node can assume that the "
"receiving node is disconnected. The response to a [`ping` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#ping) is the "
"[`pong` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#pong)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:276
msgid ""
"Before protocol version 60000, the [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#ping) had no payload. As of protocol version "
"60001 and all later versions, the message includes a single field, the "
"nonce."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:170
msgid ""
"*Added in protocol version 60001 as described by BIP31.* <br><br>Random "
"nonce assigned to this [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#ping).  The responding [`pong` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#pong) will include this nonce to identify the"
" [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#ping) to "
"which it is replying."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:282
msgid ""
"The annotated hexdump below shows a [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#ping). (The message header has been omitted.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:288
msgid "pong"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:290
msgid "*Added in protocol version 60001 as described by BIP31.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:292
msgid ""
"The [`pong` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#pong) "
"replies to a [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#ping), proving to the pinging "
"[node](../resources/glossary.md#node) that the ponging node is still "
"alive. Dash Core will, by default, disconnect from any clients which have"
" not responded to a [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#ping) within 20 minutes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:294
msgid ""
"To allow nodes to keep track of latency, the [`pong` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#pong) sends back "
"the same nonce received in the [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-network-"
"control-messages.md#ping) it is replying to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:296
msgid ""
"The format of the [`pong` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#pong) is identical to the [`ping` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#ping); only the message header differs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:298
msgid "sendaddrv2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:302
msgid ""
"The `sendaddrv2` message signals support for receiving [`addrv2` "
"messages](#addrv2) (defined in "
"[BIP155](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0155.mediawiki))."
" It also implies that its sender can encode as `addrv2` and would send "
"`addrv2` messages instead of [`addr` messages](#addr) to a peer that has "
"signaled `addrv2` support by sending a `sendaddrv2` message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:304
msgid ""
"There is no payload in a `sendaddrv2` message. See the [message header "
"section](../reference/p2p-network-message-headers.md) for an example of a"
" message without a payload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:306
msgid "sendcmpct"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:308
msgid "*Added in protocol version 70209 of Dash Core as described by BIP152*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:310
msgid ""
"The [`sendcmpct` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#sendcmpct) tells the receiving "
"[peer](../resources/glossary.md#peer) whether or not to announce new "
"[blocks](../resources/glossary.md#block) using a [`cmpctblock` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md#cmpctblock). It also "
"sends the compact block protocol version it supports. The [`sendcmpct` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#sendcmpct) is "
"defined as a message containing a 1-byte integer followed by a 8-byte "
"integer. The first integer is interpreted as a boolean and should have a "
"value of either 1 or 0. The second integer is be interpreted as a little-"
"endian version number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:312
msgid ""
"Upon receipt of a [`sendcmpct` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#sendcmpct) with the first and second integers set to 1, the "
"[node](../resources/glossary.md#node) should announce new blocks by "
"sending a [`cmpctblock` message](../reference/p2p-network-data-"
"messages.md#cmpctblock)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:314
msgid ""
"Upon receipt of a [`sendcmpct` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#sendcmpct) with the first integer set to 0, the node "
"shouldn't announce new blocks by sending a [`cmpctblock` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md#cmpctblock), but "
"instead announce new blocks by sending invs or "
"[headers](../resources/glossary.md#header), as defined by "
"[BIP130](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0130.mediawiki)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:316
msgid ""
"Upon receipt of a [`sendcmpct` message](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#sendcmpct) with the second integer set to something other "
"than 1, nodes should treat the peer as if they had not received the "
"message (as it indicates the peer will provide an unexpected encoding in "
"[`cmpctblock` messages](../reference/p2p-network-data-"
"messages.md#cmpctblock), and/or other, messages). This allows future "
"versions to send duplicate [`sendcmpct` messages](../reference/p2p-"
"network-control-messages.md#sendcmpct) with different versions as a part "
"of a version handshake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:318
msgid ""
"Nodes should check for a protocol version of >= 70209 before sending "
"[`sendcmpct` messages](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#sendcmpct). Nodes shouldn't send a request for a "
"`MSG_CMPCT_BLOCK` object to a peer before having received a [`sendcmpct` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md#sendcmpct) from "
"that peer. Nodes shouldn't request a `MSG_CMPCT_BLOCK` object before "
"having sent all [`sendcmpct` messages](../reference/p2p-network-control-"
"messages.md#sendcmpct) to that peer which they intend to send, as the "
"peer cannot know what protocol version to use in the response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-control-messages.md:320
msgid ""
"The structure of a [`sendcmpct` message](../reference/p2p-network-"
"control-messages.md#sendcmpct) is defined below."
msgstr ""

