"A sequence of bits packed eight in a byte with the least significant bit "
"first.  May be padded to the nearest byte boundary but must not contain "
"any more bits than that.  Used to assign the hashes to particular nodes "
"in the merkle tree as described below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:606
msgid ""
"The annotated hexdump below shows a [`merkleblock` message](../reference"
"/p2p-network-data-messages.md#merkleblock) which corresponds to the "
"examples below.  (The message header has been omitted.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:634
msgid ""
"Note: when fully decoded, the above [`merkleblock` message](../reference"
"/p2p-network-data-messages.md#merkleblock) provided the TXID for a single"
" transaction that matched the filter. In the "
"[network](../resources/glossary.md#network) traffic dump this output was "
