"immediately after the [`merkleblock` message](../reference/p2p-network-"
"data-messages.md#merkleblock) as a [`tx` message](../reference/p2p-"
"network-data-messages.md#tx)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:636
msgid "Parsing A MerkleBlock Message"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:638
msgid ""
"As seen in the annotated hexdump above, the [`merkleblock` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md#merkleblock) provides "
"three special data types: a transaction count, a list of hashes, and a "
"list of one-bit flags."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:640
msgid ""
"You can use the transaction count to construct an empty [merkle "
"tree](../resources/glossary.md#merkle-tree). We'll call each entry in the"
" tree a node; on the bottom are TXID nodes---the hashes for these nodes "
"are [TXIDs](../resources/glossary.md#transaction-identifiers); the "
"remaining nodes (including the [merkle root](../resources/glossary.md"
"#merkle-root)) are non-TXID nodes---they may actually have the same hash "
"as a TXID, but we treat them differently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:642
msgid ""
"![Example Of Parsing A MerkleBlock Message](../../img/dev/animated-en-"
"merkleblock-parsing.gif)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:642
msgid "Example Of Parsing A MerkleBlock Message"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:644
msgid ""
"Keep the hashes and flags in the order they appear in the [`merkleblock` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md#merkleblock). When we "
"say \"next flag\" or \"next hash\", we mean the next flag or hash on the "
"list, even if it's the first one we've used so far."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:646
msgid ""
"Start with the merkle root node and the first flag. The table below "
"describes how to evaluate a flag based on whether the node being "
"processed is a TXID node or a non-TXID node. Once you apply a flag to a "
"node, never apply another flag to that same node or reuse that same flag "
"again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid "Flag"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid "TXID Node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid "Non-TXID Node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid "**0**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid ""
"Use the next hash as this node's TXID, but this transaction didn't match "
"the filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid ""
"Use the next hash as this node's hash.  Don't process any descendant "
"nodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid "**1**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid ""
"Use the next hash as this node's TXID, and mark this transaction as "
"matching the filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:591
msgid ""
"The hash needs to be computed.  Process the left child node to get its "
"hash; process the right child node to get its hash; then concatenate the "
"two hashes as 64 raw bytes and hash them to get this node's hash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:653
msgid ""
"Any time you begin processing a node for the first time, evaluate the "
"next flag. Never use a flag at any other time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:655
msgid ""
"When processing a child node, you may need to process its children (the "
"grandchildren of the original node) or further-descended nodes before "
"returning to the parent node. This is expected---keep processing depth "
"first until you reach a TXID node or a non-TXID node with a flag of 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:657
msgid ""
"After you process a TXID node or a non-TXID node with a flag of 0, stop "
"processing flags and begin to ascend the tree. As you ascend, compute the"
" hash of any nodes for which you now have both child hashes or for which "
"you now have the sole child hash. See the [merkle tree "
"section](../reference/block-chain-block-headers.md#merkle-trees) for "
"hashing instructions. If you reach a node where only the left hash is "
"known, descend into its right child (if present) and further descendants "
"as necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:659
msgid ""
"However, if you find a node whose left and right children both have the "
"same hash, fail.  This is related to CVE-2012-2459."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:661
msgid ""
"Continue descending and ascending until you have enough information to "
"obtain the hash of the merkle root node. If you run out of flags or "
"hashes before that condition is reached, fail. Then perform the following"
" checks (order doesn't matter):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:663
msgid "Fail if there are unused hashes in the hashes list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:665
msgid ""
"Fail if there are unused flag bits---except for the minimum number of "
"bits necessary to pad up to the next full byte."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:667
msgid ""
"Fail if the hash of the merkle root node is not identical to the merkle "
"root in the [block header](../resources/glossary.md#block-header)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:669
msgid ""
"Fail if the block header is invalid. Remember to ensure that the hash of "
"the header is less than or equal to the [target "
"threshold](../resources/glossary.md#target) encoded by the nBits header "
"field. Your program should also, of course, attempt to ensure the header "
"belongs to the best block chain and that the user knows how many "
"confirmations this block has."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:671
msgid ""
"For a detailed example of parsing a [`merkleblock` message](../reference"
"/p2p-network-data-messages.md#merkleblock), please see the corresponding "
"[merkle block examples section](../examples/p2p-network-"
"parsing-a-merkleblock.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:673
msgid "Creating A MerkleBlock Message"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:675
msgid ""
"It's easier to understand how to create a [`merkleblock` "
"message](../reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md#merkleblock) after you"
" understand how to parse an already-created message, so we recommend you "
"read the parsing section above first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-data-messages.md:677
msgid ""
"Create a complete merkle tree with [TXIDs](../resources/glossary.md"
"#transaction-identifiers) on the bottom row and all the other hashes "
"calculated up to the [merkle root](../resources/glossary.md#merkle-root) "
"on the top row. For each transaction that matches the filter, track its "
"TXID node and all of its ancestor nodes."
msgstr ""

