" omitted.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-instantsend-messages.md:41
msgid "isdlock"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-instantsend-messages.md:48
msgid ""
"As of protocol version 70237, the `cycleHash` field represents the DKG "
"cycle starting block of the signing quorum instead of the DKG cycle "
"starting block corresponding to the current chain height. This change is "
"fully backwards compatible with older versions of Dash Core."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-instantsend-messages.md:51
msgid ""
"The [`isdlock` message](../reference/p2p-network-instantsend-"
"messages.md#isdlock) is used to provide details of transactions that have"
" been locked by InstantSend. The message includes all details present in "
"the deprecated [`islock` message](../reference/p2p-network-deprecated-"
"messages.md#islock) along with additional version and cycle information "
"introduced by "
"[DIP22](https://github.com/dashpay/dips/blob/master/dip-0022.md). This "
"enables nodes to determine what quorum signed the message and validate "
"the signature in the future after the quorum is no longer active. "
"Additional details about the change are available in [DIP22 - Making "
"InstantSend Deterministic using Quorum "
"Cycles](https://github.com/dashpay/dips/blob/master/dip-0022.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-instantsend-messages.md:53
msgid ""
"The request ID for an isdlock can be calculated deterministically using "
"the formula: `hash(\"islock\" + serialized_inputs)`, where \"islock\" is "
"a string prefix and the inputs are serialized in their COutPoint format. "
"This ID is used for quorum signature verification and can be obtained via"
" the [`getislocks` RPC command](../api/remote-procedure-calls-raw-"
"transactions.md#getislocks)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-instantsend-messages.md:47
#: ../../docs/core/reference/p2p-network-quorum-messages.md:155
#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-special-transactions.md
