#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md
#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:7
msgid "Address Conversion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md
msgid ""
"The hashes used in P2PKH and P2SH outputs are commonly encoded as Dash "
"addresses. This is the procedure to encode those hashes and decode the "
"addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:9
msgid ""
"The hashes used in P2PKH and [P2SH outputs](../resources/glossary.md"
"#p2sh-output) are commonly encoded as Dash "
"[addresses](../resources/glossary.md#address).  This is the procedure to "
"encode those hashes and decode the addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:11
msgid "Conversion Process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:13
msgid ""
"First, get your hash.  For P2PKH, you RIPEMD-160(SHA256()) hash a ECDSA "
"[public key](../resources/glossary.md#public-key) derived from your "
"256-bit ECDSA [private key](../resources/glossary.md#private-key) (random"
" data). For P2SH, you RIPEMD-160(SHA256()) hash a [redeem "
"script](../resources/glossary.md#redeem-script) serialized in the format "
"used in [raw transactions](../resources/glossary.md#raw-transaction) "
"(described in a [following sub-section](../reference/transactions-raw-"
"transaction-format.md)).  Taking the resulting hash:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:15
msgid ""
"Add an [address](../resources/glossary.md#address) version byte in front "
"of the hash.  The version bytes commonly used by Dash are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:17
msgid ""
"0x4c for [P2PKH addresses](../resources/glossary.md#p2pkh-address) on the"
" main Dash network ([mainnet](../resources/glossary.md#mainnet))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:19
msgid ""
"0x8c for [P2PKH addresses](../resources/glossary.md#p2pkh-address) on the"
" Dash testing network ([testnet](../resources/glossary.md#testnet))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:21
msgid ""
"0x10 for [P2SH addresses](../resources/glossary.md#p2sh-address) on "
"[mainnet](../resources/glossary.md#mainnet)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:23
msgid ""
"0x13 for [P2SH addresses](../resources/glossary.md#p2sh-address) on "
"[testnet](../resources/glossary.md#testnet)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:25
msgid ""
"Create a copy of the version and hash; then hash that twice with SHA256: "
"`SHA256(SHA256(version . hash))`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:27
msgid ""
"Extract the first four bytes from the double-hashed copy. These are used "
"as a checksum to ensure the base hash gets transmitted correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:29
msgid ""
"Append the checksum to the version and hash, and encode it as a "
"[base58](../resources/glossary.md#base58) string: `BASE58(version . hash "
". checksum)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:31
msgid "Example Code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:33
msgid ""
"Dash's base58 encoding, called "
"[Base58Check](../resources/glossary.md#base58check) may not match other "
"implementations. Tier Nolan provided the following example encoding "
"algorithm to the Bitcoin Wiki [Base58Check "
"encoding](https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Base58Check_encoding) page under the"
" [Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 "
"license](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:55
msgid ""
"Dash's own code can be traced using the [base58 header "
"file](https://github.com/dashpay/dash/blob/master/src/base58.h)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-address-conversion.md:57
msgid ""
"To convert addresses back into hashes, reverse the base58 encoding, "
"extract the checksum, repeat the steps to create the checksum and compare"
" it against the extracted checksum, and then remove the version byte."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md
#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md:7
msgid "CompactSize Unsigned Integers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md
msgid ""
"CompactSize unsigned integers are used in the raw transaction format and "
"peer-to-peer network messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md:9
msgid ""
"The [raw transaction](../resources/glossary.md#raw-transaction) format "
"and several peer-to-peer network messages use a type of variable-length "
"integer to indicate the number of bytes in a following piece of data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md:11
msgid ""
"Dash Core code and this document refers to these variable length integers"
" as compactSize. Many other documents refer to them as var_int or varInt,"
" but this risks conflation with other variable-length integer encodings"
"---such as the CVarInt class used in Dash Core for serializing data to "
"disk.  Because it's used in the transaction format, the format of "
"compactSize unsigned integers is part of the [consensus "
"rules](../resources/glossary.md#consensus-rules)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md:13
msgid ""
"For numbers from 0 to 252 (0xfc), compactSize unsigned integers look like"
" regular unsigned integers. For other numbers up to 0xffffffffffffffff, a"
" byte is prefixed to the number to indicate its length---but otherwise "
"the numbers look like regular unsigned integers in little-endian order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md
msgid "Bytes Used"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md
msgid ">= 0 && <= 0xfc (252)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md
msgid ">= 0xfd (253) && <= 0xffff"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md
msgid "0xfd followed by the number as uint16_t"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md
msgid ">= 0x10000 && <= 0xffffffff"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/transactions-compactsize-unsigned-integers.md
msgid "0xfe followed by the number as uint32_t"
