#: ../../docs/core/reference/wallets.md
msgid ""
"Dash has two deterministic wallet formats – single chain wallets and "
"hierarchical deterministic (HD) wallets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/wallets.md:9
msgid "Deterministic Wallet Formats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/wallets.md:11
msgid "Type 1: Single Chain Wallets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/wallets.md:13
msgid ""
"A Type 1 deterministic [wallet](../resources/glossary.md#wallet) is the "
"simpler of the two, which can create a single series of keys from a "
"single seed. A primary weakness is that if the seed is leaked, all funds "
"are compromised, and wallet sharing is extremely limited."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/wallets.md:15
msgid "Type 2: Hierarchical Deterministic (HD) Wallets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/reference/wallets.md:19
msgid ""
"For an overview of the [HD wallet](../resources/glossary.md#hd-wallet), "
"please see the [developer guide section](../guide/wallets.md).  For "
"details, please see "
"[BIP32](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0032.mediawiki)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:5
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/information.rst:243
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:7
msgid "51 percent attack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:9
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:323
msgid ""
"The ability of someone controlling a majority of network hash rate to "
"revise transaction history and prevent new transactions from confirming."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:13
msgid ""
"A 20-byte hash formatted using base58check to produce either a P2PKH or "
"P2SH Dash address. Currently the most common way users exchange payment "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:15
msgid "Base58"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:17
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:21
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:152
msgid ""
"The method used in Dash for converting 160-bit hashes into P2PKH and P2SH"
" addresses. Also used in other parts of Dash, such as encoding private "
"keys for backup in WIP format. Not the same as other base58 "
"implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:19
msgid "Base58check"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:23
msgid "BIP32"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:25
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:240
msgid ""
"The Hierarchical Deterministic (HD) key creation and transfer protocol "
"(BIP32), which allows creating child keys from parent keys in a "
"hierarchy. Wallets using the HD protocol are called HD wallets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:27
msgid "BIP70 payment protocol"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:29
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:481
msgid ""
"The protocol defined in BIP70 (and other BIPs) which lets spenders get "
"signed payment details from receivers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:33
msgid ""
"One or more transactions prefaced by a block header and protected by "
"proof of work. Blocks are the data stored on the block chain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:35
#: ../../docs/user/wallets/dashcore/interface.rst:557
msgid "Block chain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:37
msgid ""
"A chain of blocks with each block referencing the block that preceded it."
" The most-difficult-to-recreate chain is the best block chain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:41
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:248
msgid ""
"An 80-byte header belonging to a single block which is hashed repeatedly "
"to create proof of work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:45
msgid ""
"The number of blocks preceding a particular block on a block chain. For "
"example, the genesis block has a height of zero because zero block "
"preceded it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:47
msgid "Block reward"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:49
msgid ""
"The amount that miners may claim as a reward for creating a block. Equal "
"to the sum of the [block subsidy](#block-subsidy) (newly available duffs)"
" plus the transactions fees paid by transactions included in the block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:53
msgid ""
"The amount of new Dash created in each block. It comprises the non-fee "
"part of the [block reward](#block-reward)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:55
msgid "Block size limit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:57
msgid ""
"The maximum size in bytes that the consensus rules allow a block to be. "
"The current block size limit is 2000000 bytes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:59
msgid "Blocks-first sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:61
msgid ""
"Synchronizing the block chain by downloading each block from a peer and "
"then validating it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:63
msgid "blocktransactions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:65
msgid ""
"A P2P Networking data structure used to provide some of the transactions "
"in a block as requested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:67
msgid "blocktransactionsrequest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:69
msgid ""
"A P2P Networking data structure used to list transaction indexes in a "
"block being requested by a peer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:71
msgid "Bloom filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:73
msgid ""
"A filter used primarily by SPV clients to request only matching "
"transactions and merkle blocks from full nodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:75
msgid "Chain code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:77
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:457
msgid ""
"In HD wallets, 256 bits of entropy added to the public and private keys "
"to help them generate secure child keys; the master chain code is usually"
" derived from a seed along with the master private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:79
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/information.rst:342
msgid "ChainLock"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:81
msgid ""
"ChainLocks are a feature enabling near instant consensus on the valid "
"chain. ChainLocks use Long-Living Masternode Quorums to sign mined "
"blocks. This mitigates 51 percent attacks and reduces uncertainty when "
"receiving funds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:83
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:282
msgid "See also:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:85
msgid "[ChainLocks (Core Guide)](../guide/dash-features-chainlocks.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:86
msgid "[ChainLocks Overview (User docs)](chainlocks)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:87
msgid ""
"[DIP-8: "
"ChainLocks](https://github.com/dashpay/dips/blob/master/dip-0008.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:88
msgid "[ChainLock integration developer info](integration-chainlocks)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:90
msgid "Change output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:92
msgid ""
"An output in a transaction which returns duffs to the spender, thus "
"preventing too much of the input value from going to transaction fees."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:94
msgid "Child key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:96
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:104
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:108
msgid ""
"In HD wallets, a key derived from a parent key. The key can be either a "
"private key or a public key, and the key derivation may also require a "
"chain code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:98
msgid "Child pays for parent"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:100
msgid ""
"Selecting transactions for mining not just based on their fees but also "
"based on the fees of their ancestors (parents) and descendants "
"(children)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:102
msgid "Child private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:106
msgid "Child public key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:112
msgid ""
"A special field used as the sole input for coinbase transactions. The "
"coinbase allows claiming the block reward and provides up to 100 bytes "
"for arbitrary data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:114
msgid "Coinbase block height"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:116
msgid ""
"The current block's height encoded into the first bytes of the coinbase "
"field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:118
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/information.rst:360
msgid "Coinbase transaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:120
msgid ""
"The first transaction in a block. Always created by a miner, it includes "
"a single coinbase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:124
msgid ""
"A masternode managed, decentralized "
"[CoinJoin](https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/CoinJoin) service for creating an "
"on-demand system of removing the history from coins on the network. "
"CoinJoin processes inputs while allowing each participant to retain "
"control of their coins at all times so the process can be done without "
"trusting a third party."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:128
msgid ""
"A type of variable-length integer commonly used in the Dash P2P protocol "
"and Dash serialized data structures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:130
msgid "Compressed public key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:132
msgid ""
"An ECDSA public key that is 33 bytes long rather than the 65 bytes of an "
"uncompressed public key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:136
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:665
msgid ""
"A score indicating the number of blocks on the best block chain that "
"would need to be modified to remove or modify a particular transaction. A"
" confirmed transaction has a confirmation score of one or higher."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:138
msgid "Consensus"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:140
msgid ""
"When several nodes (usually most nodes on the network) all have the same "
"blocks in their locally-validated best block chain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:142
msgid "Consensus rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:144
msgid ""
"The block validation rules that full nodes follow to stay in consensus "
"with other nodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:146
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/features.rst:332
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/information.rst:470
msgid "Dark Gravity Wave"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:148
msgid ""
"An open source difficulty-adjusting algorithm for Bitcoin-based "
"cryptocurrencies that was first used in Dash. Difficulty adjusts every "
"block based on historical statistical data to ensure consistent block "
"issuance regardless of hash rate fluctuation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:150
msgid "Dash address encoding"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:154
msgid "Data-pushing opcode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:156
msgid ""
"Any opcode from 0x01 to 0x4e which pushes data on to the script "
"evaluation stack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:158
msgid "Decentralized Governance By Blockchain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:160
msgid ""
"The method used in Dash for funding development and making decisions "
"regarding the project direction and priorities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:162
msgid "Denominations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:164
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:184
msgid ""
"Denominations of Dash value, usually measured in fractions of a dash but "
"sometimes measured in multiples of a duff. One dash equals 100,000,000 "
"duffs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:168
msgid ""
"A development environment in which developers can obtain and spend duffs "
"that have no real-world value on a network that is very similar to the "
"Dash mainnet. Multiple independent devnets can coexist without "
"interference. Devnets can be either public or private."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:170
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/information.rst:555
msgid "Difficulty"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:172
msgid ""
"How difficult it is to find a block relative to the difficulty of finding"
" the easiest possible block. The easiest possible block has a proof-of-"
"work difficulty of 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:174
msgid "DNS seed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:176
msgid ""
"A DNS server which returns IP addresses of full nodes on the Dash network"
" to assist in peer discovery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:178
msgid "Double spend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:180
msgid ""
"A transaction that uses the same input as an already broadcast "
"transaction. The attempt of duplication, deceit, or conversion, will be "
"adjudicated when only one of the transactions is recorded in the "
"blockchain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:182
msgid "Duffs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:186
msgid "ECDSA private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:188
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:497
msgid ""
"The private portion of a keypair which can create signatures that other "
"people can verify using the public key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:190
msgid "ECDSA signatures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:192
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:553
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:593
msgid ""
"A value related to a public key which could only have reasonably been "
"created by someone who has the private key that created that public key. "
"Used in Dash to authorize spending duffs previously sent to a public key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:194
msgid "Escrow contract"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:196
msgid ""
"A transaction in which a spender and receiver place funds in a 2-of-2 (or"
" other m-of-n) multisig output so that neither can spend the funds until "
"they're both satisfied with some external outcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:198
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/features.rst:642
msgid "Evolution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:200
msgid ""
"Code name for a decentralized currency platform built on the Dash "
"blockchain technology. The goal is to provide simple access to the unique"
" features and benefits of Dash to assist in the creation of decentralized"
" technology."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:202
msgid "Extended key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:204
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:208
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:212
msgid ""
"In the context of HD wallets, a public key or private key extended with "
"the chain code to allow them to derive child keys."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:206
msgid "Extended private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:210
msgid "Extended public key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:214
msgid "Evolution masternode (EvoNode)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:216
msgid ""
"Evolution masternodes are a new type of [masternode](#masternode) created"
" to host Dash Platform – a Web3 technology stack for building "
"decentralized applications on the Dash network. The collateral required "
"to own an evonode is 4000 DASH, as opposed to 1000 DASH for regular "
"masternodes. Evonodes serve Platform along with Core, while regular "
"masternodes only serve Core. The recommended specs for evonodes are "
"higher than those for regular masternodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:218
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/information.rst:733
msgid "Fork"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:220
msgid ""
"When two or more blocks have the same block height, forking the block "
"chain. Typically occurs when two or more miners find blocks at nearly the"
" same time. Can also happen as part of an attack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:222
msgid "Genesis block"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:224
msgid "The first block in the Dash block chain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:226
msgid "Hard fork"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:228
msgid ""
"A permanent divergence in the block chain, commonly occurs when non-"
"upgraded nodes can't validate blocks created by upgraded nodes that "
"follow newer consensus rules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:230
msgid "Hardened extended key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:232
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:236
msgid ""
"A variation on HD wallet extended keys where only the hardened extended "
"private key can derive child keys. This prevents compromise of the chain "
"code plus any private key from putting the whole wallet at risk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:234
msgid "Hardened extended private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:238
msgid "HD wallet"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:242
msgid "HD wallet seed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:244
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:541
msgid ""
"A potentially-short value used as a seed to generate the master private "
"key and master chain code for an HD wallet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:246
msgid "Header"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:250
msgid "Header chain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:252
msgid ""
"A chain of block headers with each header linking to the header that "
"preceded it; the most-difficult-to-recreate chain is the best header "
"chain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:254
msgid "headerandshortids"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:256
msgid ""
"A P2P Networking data structure used to relay a block header, the short "
"transactions IDs used for matching already-available transactions, and a "
"select few transactions which a peer may be missing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:258
msgid "Headers-first sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:260
msgid ""
"Synchronizing the block chain by downloading block headers before "
"downloading the full blocks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:262
msgid "High-priority transaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:264
msgid ""
"Transactions that don't have to pay a transaction fee because their "
"inputs have been idle long enough to accumulated large amounts of "
"priority. Note: As of Dash Core 0.12.3, all transactions require a fee. "
"Also, coin age priority logic was removed in Dash Core 0.14.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:268
msgid ""
"An index number used in the HD wallet formula to generate child keys from"
" a parent key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:270
msgid "Initial block download"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:272
msgid ""
"The process used by a new node (or long-offline node) to download a large"
" number of blocks to catch up to the tip of the best block chain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:274
msgid "Input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:276
msgid ""
"An input in a transaction which contains three fields: an outpoint, a "
"signature script, and a sequence number. The outpoint references a "
"previous output and the signature script allows spending it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:280
msgid ""
"InstantSend is a service that allows for near-instant transactions. "
"Through this system, inputs can be locked to specific transactions and "
"verified by consensus of the masternode network. InstantSend allows for "
"zero-confirmation transactions to be safely accepted and re-spent prior "
"to being mined into a block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:284
msgid "[InstantSend (Core Guide)](../guide/dash-features-instantsend.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:285
msgid "[InstantSend Overview (User docs)](instantsend)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:286
msgid ""
"[DIP-10: LLMQ "
"InstantSend](https://github.com/dashpay/dips/blob/master/dip-0010.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:287
msgid "[InstantSend integration developer info](integration-instantsend)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:289
msgid "Internal byte order"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:291
msgid ""
"The standard order in which hash digests are displayed as strings---the "
"same format used in serialized blocks and transactions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:293
msgid "Inventory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:295
msgid ""
"A data type identifier and a hash; used to identify transactions, blocks,"
" and objects available for download through the Dash P2P network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:297
msgid "Key index"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:299
msgid ""
"An index number used in the HD wallet formula to generate child keys from"
" a parent key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:301
msgid "Key pair"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:303
msgid "A private key and its derived public key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:307
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:405
msgid ""
"Part of a transaction which indicates the earliest time or earliest block"
" when that transaction may be added to the block chain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:309
msgid "Long-Living Masternode Quorum"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:311
msgid ""
"Long-Living Masternode Quorums (LLMQs) are a Dash innovation that enable "
"masternodes to perform threshold signing of consensus-related messages "
"(e.g. InstantSend transactions). LLMQs provide a more scalable, general "
"use quorum system than the ephemeral ones used prior to Dash Core version"
" 0.14."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:313
msgid "M-of-N multisig"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:315
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:389
msgid ""
"A pubkey script that provides *n* number of pubkeys and requires the "
"corresponding signature script provide *m* minimum number signatures "
"corresponding to the provided pubkeys."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:319
msgid ""
"The original and main network for Dash transactions, where duffs have "
"real economic value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:321
msgid "Majority Hash Rate Attack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:325
msgid "Malleability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:327
msgid ""
"The ability of someone to change (mutate) unconfirmed transactions "
"without making them invalid, which changes the transaction's txid, making"
" child transactions invalid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:329
msgid "Master chain code and private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:331
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:335
msgid ""
"In HD wallets, the master chain code and master private key are the two "
"pieces of data derived from the root seed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:333
msgid "Master private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:339
msgid ""
"A computer that provides second-tier Dash functionality (InstantSend, "
"CoinJoin, decentralized governance). Masternodes are incentivized by "
"receiving part of the block reward, but must hold 1000 Dash as collateral"
" to prevent sybil attacks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:341
msgid "See also: [Evolution masternode](#evolution-masternode-evonode)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:343
msgid "Merkle block"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:345
msgid ""
"A partial merkle tree connecting transactions matching a bloom filter to "
"the merkle root of a block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:347
msgid "Merkle root"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:349
msgid ""
"The root node of a merkle tree, a descendant of all the hashed pairs in "
"the tree. Block headers must include a valid merkle root descended from "
"all transactions in that block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:351
msgid "Merkle tree"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:353
msgid ""
"A tree constructed by hashing paired data (the leaves), then pairing and "
"hashing the results until a single hash remains, the merkle root. In "
"Dash, the leaves are almost always transactions from a single block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:355
msgid "Message header"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:357
msgid "The four header fields prefixed to all messages on the Dash P2P network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:361
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:373
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:381
msgid ""
"Mining is the act of creating valid Dash blocks, which requires "
"demonstrating proof of work, and miners are devices that mine or people "
"who own those devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:363
msgid "Miner Activated Soft Fork"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:365
msgid "A Soft Fork activated by through miner signaling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:367
msgid "Miner fee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:369
#, python-format
msgid ""
"The amount paid to the miner who includes a transaction in a block. This "
"equals 25% of the amount remaining when the value of all outputs in a "
"transaction are subtracted from all inputs in a transaction. The "
"remaining 75% is paid to the masternode eligible for payment at the block"
" height where the transaction is mined. Related to [transaction fee"
"](#transaction-fee)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:371
msgid "Miners"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:375
msgid "Minimum relay fee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:377
msgid ""
"The minimum transaction fee a transaction must pay for a full node to "
"relay that transaction to other nodes. There is no one minimum relay fee"
"---each node chooses its own policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:383
msgid "Multi-phased fork"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:385
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:617
msgid ""
"A spork is a mechanism unique to Dash used to safely deploy new features "
"to the network through network-level variables to avoid the risk of "
"unintended network forking during upgrades. Dash Core 21.0.0 [hardened "
"all spork values on "
"mainnet](https://github.com/dashpay/dash/blob/v21.0.0/doc/release-"
"notes.md#mainnet-spork-hardening). On test networks, spork values can "
"still be updated dynamically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:393
msgid ""
"The target is the threshold below which a block header hash must be in "
"order for the block to be valid, and nBits is the encoded form of the "
"target threshold as it appears in the block header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:397
msgid "The Dash P2P network which broadcasts transactions and blocks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:399
msgid "Network magic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:401
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:633
msgid ""
"Four defined bytes which start every message in the Dash P2P protocol to "
"allow seeking to the next message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:403
msgid "nLockTime"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:407
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/information.rst:854
msgid "Node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:409
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:485
msgid "A computer that connects to the Dash network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:411
msgid "Null data (OP_RETURN) transaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:413
msgid ""
"A transaction type that adds arbitrary data to a provably unspendable "
"pubkey script that full nodes don't have to store in their UTXO database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:415
msgid "Opcode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:417
msgid ""
"Operation codes from the Dash Script language which push data or perform "
"functions within a pubkey script or signature script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:419
msgid "Orphan block"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:421
msgid ""
"Blocks whose parent block has not been processed by the local node, so "
"they can't be fully validated yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:425
msgid ""
"The data structure used to refer to a particular transaction output, "
"consisting of a 32-byte TXID and a 4-byte output index number (vout)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:427
msgid "Output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:429
msgid ""
"An output in a transaction which contains two fields: a value field for "
"transferring zero or more duffs and a pubkey script for indicating what "
"conditions must be fulfilled for those duffs to be further spent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:431
msgid "Output index"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:433
msgid ""
"The sequentially-numbered index of outputs in a single transaction "
"starting from 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:435
msgid "P2PKH address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:437
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:473
msgid ""
"A Dash payment address comprising a hashed public key, allowing the "
"spender to create a standard pubkey script that Pays To PubKey Hash "
"(P2PKH)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:439
msgid "P2SH address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:441
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:449
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:453
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:477
msgid ""
"A Dash payment address comprising a hashed script, allowing the spender "
"to create a standard pubkey script that Pays To Script Hash (P2SH). The "
"script can be almost any valid pubkey script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:443
msgid "P2SH multisig"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:445
msgid ""
"A P2SH output where the redeem script uses one of the multisig opcodes. "
"Up until Bitcoin Core 0.10.0, P2SH multisig scripts were standard "
"transactions, but most other P2SH scripts were not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:447
msgid "P2SH output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:451
msgid "P2SH pubkey script"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:455
msgid "Parent chain code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:459
msgid "Parent key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:461
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:465
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:469
msgid ""
"In HD wallets, a key used to derive child keys. The key can be either a "
"private key or a public key, and the key derivation may also require a "
"chain code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:463
msgid "Parent private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:467
msgid "Parent public key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:471
msgid "Pay To PubKey Hash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:475
msgid "Pay To Script Hash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:479
msgid "Payment protocol"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:483
msgid "Peer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:487
msgid "Point function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:489
msgid "The ECDSA function used to create a public key from a private key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:491
msgid "Previous block header hash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:493
msgid ""
"A field in the block header which contains the SHA256(SHA256()) hash of "
"the previous block's header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:495 ../../docs/user/wallets/web.rst:27
msgid "Private key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:499
#: ../../docs/user/introduction/information.rst:898
#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/advanced.rst:27
msgid "PrivateSend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:501
msgid ""
"A masternode managed, decentralized CoinJoin service for creating an on-"
"demand system of removing the history from coins on the network. CoinJoin"
" processes inputs while allowing each participant to retain control of "
"their coins at all times so the process can be done without trusting a "
"third party."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:503
msgid "Proof of work"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:505
msgid ""
"A hash below a target value which can only be obtained, on average, by "
"performing a certain amount of brute force work---therefore demonstrating"
" proof of work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:507
msgid "Pubkey script"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:509
msgid ""
"A script included in outputs which sets the conditions that must be "
"fulfilled for those duffs to be spent. Data for fulfilling the conditions"
" can be provided in a signature script. Pubkey Scripts are called a "
"scriptPubKey in code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:511
msgid "Public key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:513
msgid ""
"The public portion of a keypair which can be used to verify signatures "
"made with the private portion of the keypair."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:515
msgid "Raw block"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:517
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:565
msgid ""
"A complete block in its binary format---the same format used to calculate"
" total block byte size; often represented using hexadecimal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:519
msgid "Raw format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:521
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:525
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:569
msgid ""
"Complete transactions in their binary format; often represented using "
"hexadecimal. Sometimes called raw format because of the various Dash Core"
" commands with \"raw\" in their names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:523
msgid "Raw transaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:527
msgid "Replace-by-fee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:529
msgid ""
"NOT IMPLEMENTED IN DASH. Replacing one version of an unconfirmed "
"transaction with a different version of the transaction that pays a "
"higher transaction fee. May use BIP125 signaling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:531
msgid "Redeem script"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:533
msgid ""
"A script similar in function to a pubkey script. One copy of it is hashed"
" to create a P2SH address (used in an actual pubkey script) and another "
"copy is placed in the spending signature script to enforce its "
"conditions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:535
msgid "Regression test mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:537
msgid ""
"A local testing environment in which developers can almost instantly "
"generate blocks on demand for testing events, and can create private "
"duffs with no real-world value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:539
msgid "Root seed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:543
msgid "RPC byte order"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:545
msgid ""
"A hash digest displayed with the byte order reversed; used in Dash Core "
"RPCs, many block explorers, and other software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:547
msgid "scriptSig"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:549
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:601
msgid ""
"Data generated by a spender which is almost always used as variables to "
"satisfy a pubkey script. Signature Scripts are called scriptSig in code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:551
msgid "secp256k1 signatures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:557
msgid ""
"An autonomous agent for persisting, processing and automating Dash "
"governance objects and tasks, and for expanded functions in Dash "
"Evolution. **Note**: Sentinel was deprecated in Dash Core v20.0 when its "
"functionality was integrated into Dash Core."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:559
msgid "Sequence number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:561
msgid ""
"Part of all transactions. A number intended to allow unconfirmed time-"
"locked transactions to be updated before being finalized; not currently "
"used except to disable locktime in a transaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:563
msgid "Serialized block"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:567
msgid "Serialized transaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:571
msgid "SIGHASH flag"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:573
#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:597
msgid ""
"A flag to Dash signatures that indicates what parts of the transaction "
"the signature signs. (The default is SIGHASH_ALL.) The unsigned parts of "
"the transaction may be modified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:575
msgid "SIGHASH_ALL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:577
msgid ""
"Default signature hash type which signs the entire transaction except any"
" signature scripts, preventing modification of the signed parts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:579
msgid "SIGHASH_ANYONECANPAY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:581
msgid "A signature hash type which signs only the current input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:583
msgid "SIGHASH_NONE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:585
msgid ""
"Signature hash type which only signs the inputs, allowing anyone to "
"change the outputs however they'd like."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:587
msgid "SIGHASH_SINGLE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:589
msgid ""
"Signature hash type that signs the output corresponding to this input "
"(the one with the same index value), this input, and any other inputs "
"partially. Allows modification of other outputs and the sequence number "
"of other inputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/core/resources/glossary.md:595
msgid "Signature hash"
msgstr ""

