#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:228
msgid "Can Dash Electrum create and sign raw transactions?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:230
msgid ""
"Dash Electrum lets you create and sign raw transactions right from the "
"user interface using a form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:234
msgid "Dash Electrum freezes when I try to send Dash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:236
msgid ""
"This might happen if you are trying to spend a large number of "
"transactions outputs (for example, if you have collected hundreds of "
"donations from a Dash faucet). When you send Dash, Dash Electrum looks "
"for unspent coins that are in your wallet in order to create the new "
"transaction. Unspent coins can have different values, much like physical "
"coins and bills."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:243
msgid ""
"If this happens, you should consolidate your transaction inputs by "
"sending smaller amounts of Dash to one of your wallet addresses; this "
"would be the equivalent of exchanging a stack of nickels for a dollar "
"bill."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:251
msgid "What is the gap limit?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:253
msgid ""
"The gap limit is the maximum number of consecutive unused addresses in "
"your deterministic sequence of addresses. Dash Electrum uses it in order "
"to stop looking for addresses. In Dash Electrum 2.0, it is set to 20 by "
"default, so the client will get all addresses until 20 unused addresses "
"are found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:260
msgid "How can I pre-generate new addresses?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:262
msgid ""
"Dash Electrum will generate new addresses as you use them, until it hits "
"the `gap limit`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:265
msgid ""
"If you need to pre-generate more addresses, you can do so by typing "
"wallet.create_new_address() in the console. This command will generate "
"one new address. Note that the address will be shown with a red "
"background in the address tab, to indicate that it is beyond the gap "
"limit. The red color will remain until the gap is filled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:271
msgid ""
"WARNING: Addresses beyond the gap limit will not automatically be "
"recovered from seed. To recover them will require either increasing the "
"client’s gap limit or generating new addresses until the used addresses "
"are found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:276
msgid ""
"If you wish to generate more than one address, you may use a ‘for’ loop. "
"For example, if you wanted to generate 50 addresses, you could do this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:283
msgid "How to upgrade Dash Electrum?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:285
msgid "Warning: always save your wallet seed on paper before doing an upgrade."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:287
msgid ""
"To upgrade Dash Electrum, just :ref:`install <electrum-installation>` the"
" most recent version. The way to do this will depend on your OS. Note "
"that your wallet files are stored separately from the software, so you "
"can safely remove the old version of the software if your OS does not do "
"it for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:293
msgid ""
"Some Dash Electrum upgrades will modify the format of your wallet files. "
"For this reason, it is not recommended to downgrade Dash Electrum to an "
"older version once you have opened your wallet file with the new version."
" The older version will not always be able to read the new wallet file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:299
msgid ""
"The following issues should be considered when upgrading Dash Electrum "
"1.x wallets to Dash Electrum 2.x:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:302
msgid ""
"Dash Electrum 2.x will need to regenerate all of your addresses during "
"the upgrade process. Please allow it time to complete, and expect it to "
"take a little longer than usual for Dash Electrum to be ready."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:306
msgid ""
"The contents of your wallet file will be replaced with a Dash Electrum 2 "
"wallet. This means Dash Electrum 1.x will no longer be able to use your "
"wallet once the upgrade is complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:310
msgid ""
"The **Addresses** tab will not show any addresses the first time you "
"launch Dash Electrum 2. This is expected behaviour. Restart Dash Electrum"
" 2 after the upgrade is complete and your addresses will be available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/faq.rst:315
msgid ""
"Offline copies of Dash Electrum will not show the addresses at all "
"because it cannot synchronize with the network. You can force an offline "
"generation of a few addresses by typing the following into the Console: "
"`wallet.synchronize()`. When it’s complete, restart Dash Electrum and "
"your addresses will once again be available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/index.rst:4
#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/index.rst:34
msgid "Dash Electrum Wallet"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/index.rst:6
msgid ""
"Dash Electrum is a light wallet which uses powerful external servers to "
"index the blockchain, while still securing the keys on your personal "
"computer. Transactions are verified on the Dash blockchain using a "
"technique called Secure Payment Verification (SPV), which only requires "
"the block headers and not the full block. This means that wallet startup "
"is almost instant, while still keeping your funds secure and mobile. Dash"
" Electrum also supports advanced InstantSend, CoinJoin and masternode "
"features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user/wallets/electrum/index.rst:15
msgid ""
"Dash Electrum is a fork of the Electrum wallet for Bitcoin. While this "
"documentation focuses on using Dash Electrum, full documentation of all "
"Bitcoin Electrum features (mostly identical in Dash Electrum) is "
"available at the `official documentation site "
"<https://docs.electrum.org>`_."
msgstr ""

